apps.name: ActiveGS iOS
apps.developerName: yoshisuga & Olivier Goguel (via SideStore Team Picks)
apps.localizedDescription:
# 2021.9

This is a fork of Olivier Goguel's ActiveGS emulator for iOS.

I've been tinkering it over the years and added some experimental features such as:

- Support for iOS 15
- Remap keyboard to supported wireless controller buttons (mFi/PS4/PS5/XBox One)
- Custom split keyboard usable in landscape mode (written in Swift)

![Simulator Screen Shot - iPhone 13 Pro Max - 2021-09-22 at 22 43 15](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/564774/134484167-3c17c2a7-1d6a-467c-ac82-d7bfae7f281b.png)

- A memory debugger/rudimentary memory-editing cheat engine (also written in Swift). Accessible via the "D" button in the right pane custom keyboard. Browse the memory map and change memory values. Not sure how the bank switching works and how it's mapped to memory but you get some representation of memory. 
![Simulator Screen Shot - iPhone 13 Pro Max - 2021-09-22 at 23 25 55](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/564774/134484125-b984318a-b089-4484-b306-b976521963c3.png)

apps.name: Feather
apps.localizedDescription:
Join https://t.me/+rvcObIvOpctiMDI9 for more.
FEATURES: -
- Altstore repo support. Supporting Legacy and 2.0 repo structures
- Import your own .ipa's.
- Inject tweaks when signing apps.
Install applications straight to your device seamlessly over the air.
- Allows multiple certificate imports for easy switching.
- Configurable signing options. (name, bundleid, version, other plist options)
- Meant to be used with Apple Accounts that are apart of ADP (Apple Developer Program). however other certificates can also work!
- Easy resigning! If you have another certificate you would like to use on an app you may resign and reinstall that same app!
- No tracking, analytics, or any of the sort. Your information such as UDID and certificates will never leave the device.

apps.name: Firebird Emu
apps.localizedDescription:
# New year, new version: Firebird 1.6

**New features:**
* New dialog for creating Flash images, which is also available in the Mobile UI! (#262) 
* Running as 64bit application on Windows is supported now (#234)
* Polish translation is available now (#207)
* CX II (/-T/CAS) calculators can now be emulated (#165)! However, with the current dumping programs you will not get a complete bootrom and booting the OS will fail.

**Improvements:**
* Multiple files can be sent in the Mobile UI and by dropping them into the main window on desktop (#279)
 Reimplemented emulation speed control: Now it's more accurate, especially on Windows
* GitHub actions now performs automated builds for Android (armeabi-v7a and arm64-v8a in one APK), macOS and Windows (32bit and 64bit) on releases and pull requests (#283, #284, #285)
* The "installer" for OS 4.5.3.14 (and later?) works now. It requires [fastboot RAM](https://hackspire.org/index.php?title=Memory-mapped_I/O_ports_on_CX#90030000_-_Fastboot_RAM) to persist state across reboots, which is now implemented.
* More accurate emulation of the On button: It's now possible to enter Press-To-Test mode (#271)
* Faster saving and loading of snapshots (#231)
* More reliable USB file transfers
* The debugger console now includes entered commands in the log
* Support for PIE (position-independent executables) on x86_64. Previously, care needed to be taken that PIE was disabled, otherwise it would crash on start. (#211)
* Building the JIT is disabled automatically if the platform does not support it (#197)
* Firebird builds on FreeBSD now (#228, #248)

**Bugfixes:**
* File access on Android got fixed (#202 and its various duplicates)
* Fix placement of keypad buttons in the touchpad area (#41)
* Various fixes for the Mobile UI layout (#201)
* The kit configuration page in the Mobile UI no longer causes the keyboard to pop up by default (#257)
* Connecting with GDB on windows works now (#259, #260)
* Some shades of grey were not displayed properly when emulating pre-CX models (#270)
* Fix crash on AArch64/arm64 when executing certain instructions
* The keypad reacts to touch events in the desktop version as well now (#292, #293)
* Some places were no longer translated correctly after the introduction of language switching in 1.5
* Keys could get stuck on focus changes. Now they're all released when the keypad loses focus (#287)
* The Ctrl key now changes color when pressed
* Emulation speed no longer remains unlimited after a failed file transfer

_Repo for Arch, Debian, Fedora, Ubuntu and openSUSE: [via OBS](https://software.opensuse.org/download.html?project=home%3AVogtinator%3Afirebird-emu&package=firebird-emu&locale=en)._

There is work in progress to implement and improve support for running in the browser on Qt for WebAssembly (#294). A preview is available on https://nspire-emus.github.io/firebird/wasm/

NOTE: BundleIdentifier changed in this version and automatic updates have been disabled until manual install occurs.

apps.name: Geode Launcher
apps.localizedDescription:
a bug fix update that was long overdue

- Certificates are no longer required for iOS 26 JIT (Geode may take longer to load but this comes with a benefit that you no longer need to import certificates)
- Fixed issue with Safe Mode giving a "No certificate found" error for Enterprise Mode
- Rephrased that AltStore can be used to import certificate
- Allowed importing certificates on LiveContainer (somewhat)

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.4.1...v1.4.2

versions.localizedDescription:
a bug fix update that was long overdue

- Certificates are no longer required for iOS 26 JIT (Geode may take longer to load but this comes with a benefit that you no longer need to import certificates)
- Fixed issue with Safe Mode giving a "No certificate found" error for Enterprise Mode
- Rephrased that AltStore can be used to import certificate
- Allowed importing certificates on LiveContainer (somewhat)

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.4.1...v1.4.2

A minor bug fix update
# Changelog
- Fixed certificate being required for devices not on iOS 26
- Fixed LiveContainer not setting the environment variable if TXM is true

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.4.0...v1.4.1

An update that brings JIT support to iOS 26! With the addition of many features and fixes!
## Changelog
- Added **JIT support for iOS 26**, utilizing StikDebug (Please attach the TuliphookJIT.js script to Geode in StikDebug or wait for an update for it to automatically assign it) (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/70)
- Added a new **Aspect Ratio** setting to change the Aspect Ratio of GD. (Only works with JIT and JIT-Less)
- Updated Helper error text if it's outdated to give exactly what to do
- Added an experimental **Platform Console** for Developers
- Fixed issue where tapping **Import Certificate Manually** while the app is signed without entitlements causes a different error than what is expected to show
- Fixed grammar mistake with "launcher" when tapping **Force Reset Patching**

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.3.2...v1.4.0

Small update but an important one for mods that patch in JIT-less!
## Changelog
- Fixed patching issue with JIT-less where it doesn't patch the right size

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.3.1...v1.3.2

## Changelog
- Fixed JIT-Less crash upon playing any SFX with a pitch
- Enforced reinstalling the Helper if checksums don't match (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/75)

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.3.0...v1.3.1

## Changelog
- Added Experimental Enterprise Certificate support, aka Enterprise Mode! (View the guide on how to install!)
- Added JIT-Less support for LiveContainer (View the guide on how to install!)
- Added **9 new app icons**!
- Changed binary name to be just Geode (to make it easier to find crashlogs)
- Added :fish:
- Added an option to allow you to import a certificate manually if you sideloaded with SideStore
- Manually reopening in LiveContainer is no longer required
- Fixed Invalid Signature (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/66)
- Fixed error with "color.done" not being "Done"

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.2.0...v1.3.0

## Changelog
- Added **Trans** icon
- Made launching with JIT-less much more quicker (reducing signing & patching)
- Added a JIT-less diagnose view
- Removed the requirement of mobile provision file when importing certificate (p12 file is now only needed)
- Fixed iOS 26 beta 2 from crashing upon launch (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/57)
- Fixed safe mode not only patching with Geode and instead patching with other mods
- Fixed mods sometimes not patching unless the game is relaunched

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.1.0...v1.2.0

## Changelog
- Added experimental JIT-less support!
- Fixed issue with automatic launching automatically launching in TIPA version if you go back to the app.

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing. It will be updated in the future for a guide on JIT-less.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.0.1...v1.1.0

## Changelog
- Fixed StikJIT and other apps not opening automatically when pressing launch

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v1.0.0...v1.0.1

Finally at **v1.0.0**! This adds a new icon to celebrate Pride Month, fixes bugs, and more!

## Changelog
- Added icon selection
- Added **Pride Month** icon
- Added a warning if you launch Geode with JIT without having it launch in the containerized Geometry Dash (Mainly for those that think they need to **always** launch Geode with JIT when that isn't the case) (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/35)
- Fixed bug with JIT enabler crashing on iPad when tapped on (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/37)
- Fixed bug with the launcher not knowing if Geode dylib is up to date or not (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/36)
- Fixed bug with not being able to exit settings if you're on landscape rotation in iPhone (https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/issues/47)
- Fixed Trollstore version of the launcher not rendering color wheel (uses image instead)
- Fixed issue with color selection being impossible to exit on iPad

View the [INSTALL.md](https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/blob/main/INSTALL.md) guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v0.5.1...v1.0.0

## Changelog
- Added Trollstore warning to tell you to enable "URL Scheme" in settings
- Removed Nightly being enabled by default
- Added landscape rotation support for phones
- Fixed bug where cancelling the update early for Geode will assume Geode was updated for nightly releases
- Fixed Trollstore version of the launcher crashing when going to color picker

**Expect bugs!**

View the INSTALL.md guide on installing.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/geode-sdk/ios-launcher/compare/v0.5.0...v0.5.1

apps.localizedDescription:
Version 1.10.8 fixes the cover art system, thus closing #190. ~~There also appears to be an issue with the previous Cydia release being corrupted, so hopefully, that is fixed in this version.~~

**Full Changelog**
- Fixed cover art system (#203). Thanks, @unlmtd.

versions.localizedDescription:
Version 1.10.8 fixes the cover art system, thus closing #190. ~~There also appears to be an issue with the previous Cydia release being corrupted, so hopefully, that is fixed in this version.~~

**Full Changelog**
- Fixed cover art system (#203). Thanks, @unlmtd.
- Fixed compilation errors (#191). Thanks, @jdkula.

iNDS is a derivation of the previous Nintendo DS apps for iOS, nds4ios and Nitrogen. The iNDS Team release of iNDS is a fork of the original iNDS emulator by William Cobb. iNDS Team aims to create a version that is driven by support from the community, adding trusted contributors to the team over time, so that pull requests and issues do not sit untouched.

Currently, emulation is powered by the DeSmuME threaded ARM interpreter and runs at nearly full speed on the iPhone 5 and above. Due to the need to mmap the entire ROM into memory, older devices with only 256MB of RAM are not supported. These devices include the iPod touch 4, iPad 1, iPhone 3GS, and anything below those devices.

apps.name: iSH
apps.developerName: Theodore Dubois and contributors (via SideStore Team Picks)
apps.localizedDescription:
New stuff:
- iSH now supports custom themes
- Preferences are now exposed via procfs
- Some more app icon choices
- Hyperlinks created by OSC 8 are underlined instead of invisible

Fixed bugs:
- Forward SO_RCVTIMEO, SO_SNDTIMEO in setsockopts to support snac
- Add about four dozen SIMD instructions to improve support for nodejs and Rust
- Fix bottom keyboard inset for iPad, Stage Manager, and devices with no home button
- Implement /proc/pid/task to fix recent versions of GDB
- Fix VoiceOver focus stealing keyboard focus on iOS 15+
- Resolve an issue with xadd causing git clones to hang
- Trigger segfault on unaligned cmpxchg8b, which iSH does not support
- Fix a race condition that causes some output to be lost
- Fix toolbar button sizing

- Hyperlinks created by OSC 8 are underlined instead of invisible

Fixed bugs:
- Forward SO_RCVTIMEO, SO_SNDTIMEO in setsockopts to support snac
- Add about four dozen SIMD instructions to improve support for nodejs and Rust
- Fix bottom keyboard inset for iPad, Stage Manager, and devices with no home button
- Implement /proc/pid/task to fix recent versions of GDB
- Fix VoiceOver focus stealing keyboard focus on iOS 15+
- Resolve an issue with xadd causing git clones to hang
- Trigger segfault on unaligned cmpxchg8b, which iSH does not support
- Fix a race condition that causes some output to be lost
- Fix toolbar button sizing

Kodi is available for multiple operating-systems and hardware platforms, featuring a 10-foot user interface for use with televisions and remote controls. It allows users to play and view most videos, music, podcasts, and other digital media files from local and network storage media and the internet.

versions.localizedDescription:
Play your PSP games in HD!
PPSSPP can run your PSP games on your PC in full HD resolution, and play them on Android too. It can even upscale textures that would otherwise be too blurry as they were made for the small screen of the original PSP.

Even on modern Android phones and tablets, you can often run at double the original resolution.

Enhance your experience!
Play in HD resolutions and more
Play on a tablet for big-screen mobile gaming
Customize on-screen touch controls or use an external controller or keyboard
Save and restore game state anywhere, anytime
Crank up the anisotropic filtering and texture scaling
Continue where you left off by transferring saves from your real PSP
Free & Open Source
PPSSPP is an open source project, licensed under the GPL 2.0 (or later). Anyone is welcome to contribute improvements to the code. Partly thanks to such contributions, PPSSPP's compatibility is steadily increasing, letting us all play our PSP games on the devices of our choice.

Hey there side commmunity. This is a patch to improve stability of sidestore. more specifically for sources.

We got another update, just in time for Christmas! (depending on where you live)

Before we bring in 0.6.0 with AltStore 2.0 fully merged, consider this as a point update for all the fun things we made before it!

## What's Changed
* feat: show custom anisette server list if set by @moonsn in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/717
* Fix for Refresh Operation causing renewal/install of provisioning profiles for removed app extensions by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/727
* Fix-regression: restored update-check logic(2a392dd) in InstalledApp.swift which was dropped in (1713fcc) by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/728
* xcode: Debug dylib support is still broken in iOS 18 causing No Entry Point Found. checked(null) by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/729
* refresh-app: enhanced error logging when app extension validation check fails by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/730
* diagnostics: improved error logging for OperationError.invalidParameters by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/736
* -[cleanup]: restore changes dropped from altstore-1.6.3 merge by 1713fcc by @mahee96 in https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/738

# Changelog
* Remove the buggy retry code finally (@nythepegasus)
* Recompile and update AltBackup to make it function again (@nythepegasus)
* Update submodule dependencies (@naturecodevoid and @nythepegasus)

Having a good September? We have been hard at work on stability improvements and better error logging for SideStore!

# Changes 

 * The Unable to install app (aka staging error) error message has been split into explicit error messages. This should allow people who get the error to troubleshoot more easily. (Dadoum for initial implementation, naturecodevoid for fixes)
* AltSign and all other dependencies were updated. This should help fix some issues. (spidy123222 and Joelle Lonkell for AltSign, naturecodevoided for everything else)
* The notification and alert explaining SideStore needing to be in the background to refresh was shortened and made clearer. (spidy123322)
Full Changelog: https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/compare/0.5.0..0.5.1

Happy July! We have been hard at work on stability improvements for SideStore!

# Changes 

 * [bugfix] Widget now functions properly from Github Actions builds
* [bugfix] Installing and refreshing apps should be much more stable
* [bugfix] Reintroduce notification when refreshing SideStore
* [feature] Add retries to enabling JIT to make it a little more stable
* [feature] Change the default anisette server to be https://ani.sidestore.io/ instead of the 6969 port (which no longer exists)
* [UI] Change the Patreon screen to display our different social media accounts
* [upstream] Fix many deprecation warnings
* [upstream] Fix "Open in.." file dialog not working for SideStore
* [upstream] Fix various UI elements to be more performant/less buggy
Full Changelog: https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/compare/0.4.0..0.5.0

Happy May! We have been very busy with doing quality of life changes and fixing bugs everyone‚Äôs been having. WE RECOMMEND FRESH INSTALL ON THIS UPDATE. it took this long as there was some problems that were hard and some things needed fixed before releasing and testing, but this should make sidestore much better to use. If you ever want to test sidestore versions use nightly version of sidestore. If you‚Äôre into even more experimental join our discord and try our ipas we ask for testing. 

 For people that want to use MDC no3applimit (MacDirtyCow). It‚Äôs currently not ready as it includes the patch not needing any external apps. So for any brave people that really want it you will have to look at this pull request and use the ipa downloads from GitHub actions  https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/259 or get it from our site as a ipa labeled MDC.

 What's Changed: 

 - Fix: Fix expire early issue (it will open safari to finish refreshing sidestore now.) 

 - Updated to Anisette V3, this is much better than version 1 as it prevents locking and other anisette issues. 

 - Fix: no provisioning profile with the requested identifier. 

 - Remove jkcoxson anisette server from preferred servers. 

 - Update store check to check for AltServer or SideServer installation 

 - refactor minimuxer to use swift-bridge (#321) 

 - Change the default anisette server 

 - fix: hopefully reduce ApplicationVerificationFailed errors by removing _CodeSignature folders since those may cause a problems. 

 - Fix: 'The name for this app is invalid' error(#361). 

 - Remove app groups that contain AltStore 

 - Change SideStore Anisette server url to use https. Full Commit Changelog: https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/compare/0.3.1...0.4.0

Happy March! We have been busy with doing quality of life changes and getting stuff up and running like deactivating and getting bugs fixed that you guys found in nightly. We don‚Äôt currently have a fix for expiring early issue but is in the works like anisette issues. This should allow basic support for all functions.

 For people that want to use MDC no3applimit (MacDirtyCow). It‚Äôs currently not ready as it includes the patch not needing any external apps. So for any brave people that really want it you will have to look at this pull request and use the ipa downloads from GitHub actions  https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/pull/259 . We don‚Äôt recommend relying on pull requests as because a commit could break the app so be warned, this is the same for nightly but with nightly has latest develop branch changes.

 What's Changed: 

 - Fix beta apps not refreshing 

 - Fix beta apps on the my apps view 

 - Fix deactivating/activating apps 

 - Merge all of Riley's new error handling stuff 

 - add easy anisette server selector iOS Settings app 

 - added toggle for custom anisette server 

 - Change the default anisette server 

 - Add a bit more logging throughout the signing process to help us pin down issues 

 - Allow for .mobiledevicepairing and .plist files to be selected, try and pin down why users can't select either 

 - Hopefully fix AltWidget issues 

 - Add analytics to help developers understand current demographic of users (and hopefully pin down version specific bugs) 

 - Icon change (thanks LittRitt!) 

 - Sidestore directory accessible in files 

 - Reset pairing file button 

 - Advanced settings button 

 - Browse icon change 

 - Credit adjustment 

 - Background color fixes 

 - Added more permission types for sources 

 - Join Patreon button crash fix 

 - Turned off background notification refreshes 

 - Sidestore Logger 

 - Minimuxer logger 

 - Additional logging for minimuxer for sidestore for troubleshooting 

 - Replace Placeholder video for pairing instructions. 

 - Fix BundleId issues on parts of sidestore 

 - Fix trusted sources if one app has problems that it shouldn‚Äôt take down the full list. 

 

 Full Commit Changelog: https://github.com/SideStore/SideStore/compare/0.1.1...0.3.1

üî•üî•üî• Your device hurts to hold in places and performance is definitely being throttled.

VSCO, injected with the tweak Lion by Michael Lema. Allows for saving pretty much all media by long-pressing on them. Few things to note: If you're jailbroken, fully disable tweak injection into VSCO using Choicy. Signing in through Apple and Google don't work (clicking Apple does nothing, clicking Google causes a crash). If you need to sign in this way, create a backup of VSCO from the App Store using either Apps Manager or Crane, depending on if your phone is jailbroken or not, while signed in before installing this ipa through TrollStore. This version also does not include dark mode. All other features should be the same
Last updated: 12-03-2022
